Break this code intentionally:

resource "local_file" "bad" {
  filename = hello.txt
  content  = "oops"
}

👉 Fix it and explain WHY it broke

Solution :-
resource "local_file" "bad" { filename = "hello.txt" content = "oops" } 
It broke because in terraform(HCL) string should always be quoted.
So here terraform will treat hello.txt as a reference like a variable, resource or attribute not as a literal string.
Because of this terraform will throw an error.
